        "summary": "Simon discusses monetization, revenue sharing.",
        "mainText": "According to Simon, a Creator Code-like system is possible, with an option to receive revenue sharing from Hytale itself - meaning all mods could be free, but modders could still make money. A Creator Code-like system intended for mod devs would need to avoid adding complexity to accounting, and would need an automated application process. When asked about servers being Pay To Win, Simon says no official server or content would be P2W, and any P2W server wouldn't appear in the server browser. Looking to Microsoft and Roblox, Simon says Microsoft has fought to keep P2W out of Minecraft but it's a losing battle, and Roblox promotes P2W content to reap money - Hytale would only promote \"clean\" servers, potentially letting them access more things.",
